Author: cinnamonbicycle
Text: Yeah, it's kind of pointless if you're not dedicated. I see a dietitian as a condition of my outpatient treatment, but I've just been constantly losing weight and there's really nothing she can do about it. I do like her and value her expertise, but at the end of the day, I'm just really terrible at not losing weight. All she can do is threaten me with treatment but it's all empty threats once I turn 18.
